HEADWORD: Muscule
<hw>Mus"cule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>musculus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>muscule</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A long movable shed used by besiegers in ancient times in attacking
the walls of a fortified town.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

